[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Today, we\'re introducing Expo Agent. Expo is the leading open source framework for building mobile apps with JavaScript and React. And for years now, you\'ve been able to add any custom native code you want to your Expo app. But, the complexity of working with Swift, Objective-C, Java, Kotlin makes it just a little too impractical for'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'most projects, features, and developers. But, Expo Agent changes that. It\'s an agent that can write full robust native code right from your browser. We\'re talking SwiftUI and Jetpack Compose all from a conversation. The agent knows how'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and when to generate complex native code from a prompt. It plans out the best use of rich native functionality with scripting features like instant over-the-air updates, hot reloading, and server-side rendering. Let me show you.'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I asked the agent to build a quick app for the Expo blog. It spun up previews across all platforms, iOS, Android, and web. It generated the code, validated its output, and we can see the results live. Native animations, gestures,'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'everything tuned per platform. Now, on web, we ran into a little bit of an issue fetching data. It\'s CORS issue, classic. This is because we don\'t have a back end set up. So, we can just ask the agent. It can check the logs, see what\'s'

[01:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going on, and spin up a serverless API route for us instantly. This works across all platforms. And this pattern enables us to protect secrets and environment variables for third-party integrations. But, here\'s where it gets'

[01:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really fun. When you build a native app, you\'re not limited to the browsers. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; You have access to anything that the device is capable of. We can add home screen widget, rich push notifications, or even build an Apple Watch app. If you can imagine it and the device can do it,'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Expo Agent probably build it. Here, it\'s spinning up new targets, writing all the SwiftUI code, configuring entitlements, and hooking everything up to the server from earlier. And the best part is we can test all this without having to join'

